INSTALLATION OF ORACLE VM VIRTUAL BOX ON WINDOWS
1.Download the VirtualBox setup file for Windows.
2.Run the installer (.exe file).
3.Click Next → keep default options → click Install.
4.Allow network installation prompts → click Yes.
5.After installation, click Finish to open VirtualBox.
6.Click New to create a virtual machine.
7.Set Name, Type, and Version → click Next.
8.Assign RAM  → click Next.
9.Create a Virtual Hard Disk → select VDI, Dynamically allocated, set size → click Create.
10.Go to Settings → Storage, add your ISO file.
11.Click Start to boot and install the operating system.

